title: Huskerland Top Tens: Classes A, B
text: 9. Grand Island Northwest 5-110. Lincoln Pius X 3-3 Bob Sez: Plattsmouth gets the big win of the week, a 50-49 classic over Gretna; Plattsmouth moves up three spots, Gretna falls two. Pius X is new at 3-3 despite a loss - a triple overtime loss by one point to No. 2 Skutt. Pius's other two losses are to No. 3 York and No. 6 Gretna. Elkhorn South holds on to the top spot after a 62-0 win over Mount Michael and York beat Lexington 35-6 while Aurora won out west, beating Scottsbluff 26-7. Beatrice struggled but beat Omaha Gross, 20-13, while Northwest held off ratings contender Sidney, 27-20. McCook beat Gering, 14-0, in a game suspended in the first half after a lengthy lightning storm; officially, that's scored as a forfeit. Top Games for Week 7: Gretna at Omaha Skutt, Elkhorn vs. Elkhorn South, Grand Island Northwest at York, Sidney at Scottsbluff. FEATURED PRODUCTS
